cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computational modeling of phonological similarity effects in the formation of word-meaning associations. It involves the use of Automata Networks and computer simulations to study the evolution of an energy function that measures the amount of local agreement between individuals. This work is likely to be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language processing and phonological similarity effects. It may also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of computational models and simulations. Additionally, it may be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the formation of word-meaning associations on artificial populations of speakers. It may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the study of working-memory mechanisms and the evolution of an energy function.
